==French==
===Etymology===
Old French ''[[esmai]]'', from ''[[esmaier]]'' ‘to trouble’, from Vulgar Latin ''*exmagare'' ‘make someone lost, bewitch’, from Latin ''[[ex-]]'' + a second element representing either Latin ''[[magus]]'' ‘sorceror’ or Germanic ''*magan'' ‘power’ ( > English ''[[may]]'').

